The paper deals with influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and social computing (cs.SOC). The paper also proposes a submodular maximization task, which is a common topic in the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of randomized algorithms and approximation algorithms, which are topics in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.MA) and machine learning theory (cs.LG).
